## 5. Features

### Feature 1: AI-Powered Personalized Onboarding
Users name their AI companion, complete a financial profiling quiz (goals, knowledge level, risk tolerance, savings habits), and receive an AI-generated financial profile summary in plain language. This profile personalizes every subsequent interaction — lesson difficulty, recommendation style, and chatbot personality all adapt to the individual user.

### Feature 2: Interactive Budget & Expense Tracker
Full budget management with income/expense tracking, monthly comparisons, pie/bar chart breakdowns, AI-powered spending insights, savings goals with progress bars, and a dedicated expenses page with category deep-dives, recurring expense management, and spending velocity tracking.

### Feature 3: Paper Trading Portfolio with Simulated Live Market
A simulated stock market with 20+ stocks updating in real-time (every 2 seconds), a scrolling ticker bar, market index cards (S&P 500, Dow, NASDAQ, Russell 2000), live trade feed, and the ability to buy/sell stocks with zero real money at risk. Includes comprehensive investing education covering stocks, ETFs, P/E ratios, diversification, dollar-cost averaging, and risk levels.

### Feature 4: Banking Hub with Multi-Account Management
Link and switch between multiple bank accounts, view checking/savings balances and transactions per bank, compare savings and checking accounts across major institutions (Chase, Ally, Marcus, Discover), and receive AI recommendations tailored to each linked bank.

### Feature 5: Credit Card Management & Score Education
View active credit cards with balances, utilization bars, payment due dates, minimum payments, APR, and rewards breakdowns. Credit score display with factor breakdown (payment history, utilization, credit age, mix, inquiries), personalized improvement tips, score simulator with what-if scenarios, and a guided application flow for new cards with AI-powered pre-qualification advice.

### Feature 6: Retirement Planning (Roth IRA & 401K)
Roth IRA page with contribution tracker, interactive investment allocation pie chart showing actual stock holdings (click to drill down), compound growth projections, add-funds functionality, and a locked-withdrawal indicator showing the user is under 59½. 401K page with employer match optimizer, vesting schedule, fund comparison table, Traditional vs Roth comparison, and tax advantage calculator.

### Feature 7: Savings Goals & High-Yield Account Recommendations
Dedicated savings hub with total savings overview, goal-based progress tracking (emergency fund, vacation, car, college), HYSA comparisons, savings strategy education (50/30/20 rule, pay yourself first, automate), and monthly growth charts.

### Feature 8: Loan Management & Payoff Strategies
Comprehensive loan center covering Student Loans, Auto Loans, Mortgage, and Personal Loans — each with toggle on/off (hide irrelevant loan types), payoff progress bars, multiple payoff strategies (avalanche, snowball, refinancing, employer programs) with estimated impact, educational tips, key facts, and warnings about default consequences. AI provides prioritized payoff recommendations.

### Feature 9: AI Chatbot Companion
Always-available conversational AI that maintains user context (holdings, budget, goals, risk tolerance). Streams responses in real-time via SSE. Provides context-aware conversation starters. Explains financial concepts in plain language tailored to the user's knowledge level. Named by the user and referenced throughout the app for a personal experience.

### Feature 10: Financial Education Hub with Course Library
Six core lessons with progress tracking, XP/level gamification system, and an expandable course catalog of 20+ courses across 8 categories (Investing, Banking, Credit, Taxes, Insurance, Real Estate, Crypto, Business). Each course shows difficulty, duration, star ratings, student counts, and enrollment status. Search and category filtering for easy discovery.

### Feature 11: Fraud Protection Center
Security score dashboard, emergency fraud reporting numbers (FTC, Equifax, Experian, TransUnion) with one-tap copy, interactive security checklist, recent security activity feed, and fraud prevention education covering phishing, card skimming, identity theft, and online shopping safety.

### Feature 12: Personalized AI Insights Across All Pages
Every page features contextual AI recommendations from the user's named buddy — budget insights, portfolio analysis, savings tips, loan payoff strategies, credit score improvement advice, and banking recommendations. The AI name updates globally when changed in settings.

